{"link_name": "Zabbix Go loadable module", "type": "Module", "OS": "", "vendor": "", "minZabbVer": "2.2.x", "link_desc": "<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, 'Segoe UI', Arial, freesans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6000003814697px;\">This project aims to provide <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #4078c0; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"https://golang.org/\">Go</a> bindings for creating native Zabbix modules.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, 'Segoe UI', Arial, freesans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6000003814697px;\">Zabbix modules are an effective way of extending the Zabbix agent and server to monitor resources which are not natively support by Zabbix.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, 'Segoe UI', Arial, freesans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6000003814697px;\">There are currently two ways to to extend Zabbix:</p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px 0px 0px 2em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, 'Segoe UI', Arial, freesans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6000003814697px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #4078c0; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"https://www.zabbix.com/documentation/2.4/manual/config/items/userparameters\">User Parameters</a></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">and <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #4078c0; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"https://www.zabbix.com/documentation/2.4/manual/config/items/loadablemodules?s%5B%5D=module\">Loadable Modules</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, 'Segoe UI', Arial, freesans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6000003814697px;\">User Parameters simply map agent item keys to system calls. While this is by far the easiest way to extend Zabbix, User Parameters require a process fork on every call (a severe performance impact under load) and typically require a script interpreter such as Perl or Ruby and their dependent framework modules.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, 'Segoe UI', Arial, freesans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6000003814697px;\">Loadable Modules offer a significant performance increase (being native C libraries) and <em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">reduce</em> the overhead of dependencies. Unfortunately, modules are rarely adopted because the effort and expertice required to write one in C is a great deal more than writing a script in a higher level language like Perl.</p>", "features": "Loadable Module", "address": "", "city": "", "state": "", "country": "", "postcode": "", "telephone": "", "fax": "", "email": "", "website": "https://github.com/cavaliercoder/g2z", "price": 0, "link_hits": 3144, "link_votes": null, "link_rating": 0, "link_featured": null, "link_created": "2017-06-17 08:24:55", "link_modified": "2018-09-12 11:42:08", "link_visited": 710, "publish_up": "2017-06-17 08:24:55", "publish_down": "0000-00-00 00:00:00", "metakey": "", "metadesc": "", "1.8": "", "2.0": "", "2.2": "", "2.4": "", "3.0": "", "3.2": "", "3.4": "", "4.0": "", "4.2": "", "4.4": "", "5.0": "", "5.2": "", "tags": "go, golang, module", "author": "Ryan Armstrong", "user_id": 146, "link_id": 853, "cat_id": "220", "internal_notes": "", "lat": 0, "lng": 0, "zoom": ""}